  "crew_text": "OUR TRIP OBJECTIVES -- REACT / ADD BELOW\n\nGROUP: 3 adults + 3 teens (13-15), able-bodied, good travel problem-solvers\nWINDOW: Mid-June to late July\nBUDGET: $10-15K per family of 4 (2 adults + 2 teens)\n\n1. EXPLORATION INDEX\nPlaces none of us have been. Greece = high (first time) for everyone. Rome, French Riviera, and Italian Riviera are all lower here since 2 of the 6 travelers have already been to all three.\n\n2. HISTORY & CULTURE INDEX\nReal ruins, castles, archaeological sites -- walk through the story, not just photos.\n\n3. OUTDOOR / ACTIVE INDEX\nHiking, swimming, physical challenge. Teens want to move.\n\n4. MEDITERRANEAN COAST INDEX\nTurquoise water, beaches, cliffs -- core pull of the whole trip.\n\n5. FOOD INDEX\nEat like locals -- markets, tavernas, street food. No tourist traps.\n\n6. COST EFFICIENCY INDEX\nMax experience per dollar. Rural Greece beats Rome badly here.\n\n7. TRAVEL SIMPLICITY INDEX\nMinimize painful transit -- long waits and rushed city-to-city moves drain the trip.\n\n8. GROUP HARMONY INDEX\nTeens engaged + adults not bored. Mix of challenge and depth.\n\nOPEN QUESTIONS FOR THE GROUP:\n- Rome vs Naples vs Amalfi Coast for the Italy stop?\n- Comfortable with narrow mountain driving in the Peloponnese?\n- Everyone in for the Samaria Gorge hike (16km, ~6hrs)?\n- Ryanair (cheaper, bag fees) vs full-service airlines for intra-Europe legs?\n- Exact dates -- mid-June (cooler, cheaper) vs July (hotter, pricier)?\n\nReply with your top 3 priorities from the list above, or add anything missing.",
